title: Update to operations with 'psa_' prefix
body:
This commit updates the interface to use the updated protobuf contracts
that start with 'psa_' prefixes.

Signed-off-by: Ionut Mihalcea <ionut.mihalcea@arm.com>

title: Add missing_doc as an error
body:
This commit adds code documentation on every public item.
Sorry for the long PR but this is only documentation.

Signed-off-by: Hugues de Valon <hugues.devalon@arm.com>

title: Update to PSA Crypto API 1.0.0
body:
Fetches the latest changes in the operations directory to update all
operations and results to PSA Crypto 1.0.0 version.

title: Add code documentation
body:
Modifies the root crate documentation examples so that they are all
executable.
Adds more documentation here and there.

Signed-off-by: Hugues de Valon <hugues.devalon@arm.com>

title: Fix supported wire protocol version
body:
As written in the [Parsec book](https://parallaxsecond.github.io/parsec-book/parsec_client/wire_protocol.html#requests), the only allowed version is 1.0 and not
0.1!

Signed-off-by: Hugues de Valon <hugues.devalon@arm.com>

title: Add a wire protocol version check
body:
As per the discussion in parallaxsecond/parsec#105, it was decided that
the version check should happen in the front-end handler. Because there
is currently only one version supported (0.1), and it might stay like
this for a long time, this commit adds a simple check directly in the
request/response parser.
If multiple versions are supported, this would not suffice and a better
solution should be adopted but this is probably fine for now.

Signed-off-by: Hugues de Valon <hugues.devalon@arm.com>

title: Add a submodule for the operations
body:
This commit modifies the build process to directly use the git submodule
containing the protobuf files instead of downloading them from the
GitHub repository. This should allow us to publish the crate without
having it needing internet connection.

Signed-off-by: Hugues de Valon <hugues.devalon@arm.com>

title: Review ResponseStatus usage
body:
As part of parallaxsecond/parsec#72 review the ResponseStatus that we
use and remove/update the ones that we do not need.

Signed-off-by: Hugues de Valon <hugues.devalon@arm.com>

Signed-off-by: Hugues de Valon <hugues.devalon@arm.com>

title: Various lint fixes
body:
Replaces the clippy command with the one discussed in parallaxsecond/parsec#91. The
pedantic group will be discussed later.

Signed-off-by: Hugues de Valon <hugues.devalon@arm.com>

title: Add body length limit to reading requests and responses
body:
This commit adds a parameter to the `read_from_stream` methods for
requests and responses, which acts as a hard limit on the size of the
request/response body. This is to allow clients to protect themselves
from running out of memory when processing requests/responses.

title: Derive Arbitrary for fuzz testing
body:
This commits adds conditional derivation of the Arbitrary trait for the structures
and enums that require it for implementing fuzz testing.

title: Remove most panicking behaviour
body:
The following functions/macros were replaced by returning errors:
* unwrap
* panic
* expect
* unimplemented
* unreachable

Those should only be allowed in tests and were kept for the env::var
function.

Signed-off-by: Hugues de Valon <hugues.devalon@arm.com>
